Class Writer

  • java.lang.Object
    • proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.model.writing.Writer
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CSVWriter, JSONWriter

    public abstract class Writer
extends java.lang.Object
    The class all Writers have to extend. Every non abstract class that extends this class will be included in WriterFactory.allWriters

      • validate

        public boolean validate(OutputConfiguration configuration,
               Control theControl)
                 throws InvalidInputException,
                        CollectedException
        This method is called by the method OutputConfiguration.validate(proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.controller.Control). It tests, whether the specificSettings given in the OutputConfiguration are valid for this writer. Also checks whether the destination file already exists and uses Control.notifyUser(java.lang.String, java.lang.String) to ask, if the file can be overwritten.
        Parameters:
        configuration - The OutputConfiguration whose settings shall be validated
        theControl - The Control, that is used to ask the user if he wants to overwrite.
        Returns:
        True, if the settings of the OutputConfiguration are valid; otherwise an Exception is thrown
        Throws:
        InvalidInputException - to indicate, which input parameter was invalid
        CollectedException - to indicate all of the specificSettings that were invalid

      • write

        public void write(OutputConfiguration configuration,
         Intern input)
           throws InvalidInputException
        This method is called by the WriterFactory to start the writing. It opens a PrintWriter to the file specified in the configuration, and then calls the specific actuallyWrite(proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.model.description.OutputConfiguration, proteomicsdb.org.requesttool.model.description.Intern, java.io.PrintWriter) method After that it closes the PrintWriter again. It also sets the doAppend-flag of the OutputConfiguration to false, if appending is enabled, but the file is empty; this is needed because a Writer might have different behaviour if it appends then if it writes a new file; but in an empty file, this different behavior does not make sense.
        Parameters:
        configuration - The OutputConfiguration that specifies, how the data shall be written
        input - The data to be written
        Throws:
        InvalidInputException - If there occurs a problem with the destination file
